Detailed description of the dataset variables:

● opt_ID: The identifier of an opportunity.
● opt_name_data: A concatenation of data-related words found in the title of
the opportunity (a predefined list of data-related words was used to search for
matches within each opportunity title). The words are separated by spaces. 
● opt_desc_data: A concatenation of data-related words found in the
opportunity description written by the salesperson (a predefined list of
data-related words was used to search for matches within each description). If
the cell is empty, no data-related words were identified in the opportunity
description.
○ Note: Words may sometimes appear truncated (e.g., Analyti), due to
the algorithm used for extraction.
● opt_name_size: The total number of words in the opportunity's title.
● opt_desc_size: The total number of words in the opportunity's description.
● id_client: The identifier of the client.
● client_class: The classification of the client, indicating their importance to the
company (based on revenue).
● segment: The department within the company where the opportunity is
referenced.
● duration: The estimated duration of the project (in days).
● opt_class: The classification of the opportunity, indicating its importance to
the company.
● sales_capture: The first and last name of the salesperson who logged the
opportunity (data has been anonymized).
● count_aai: The total number of "AAI" opportunities identified by the
salesperson.
● pricing_structure: The agreed-upon pricing structure with the client.
● business_entity: The business entity responsible for the opportunity.
● client_location: The location where the opportunity will take place.
● competition_type: Indicates whether the company (ABC Sport Corp) is
competing to win this opportunity.
● alliances: A flag indicating whether the opportunity involves a partnership
with another data-related company.
● quarter: The fiscal year and quarter of the opportunity's sale (e.g., FY20Q3 =
Q3 2020).
● mergers: A flag indicating whether the opportunity will be led by a subsidiary
of the company and is related to data.
● stage: The progress status of the opportunity (0 being the least advanced, 3B
being the most advanced). Opportunities in earlier stages are generally less
detailed, as salespeople update them progressively.
● win_prob: The salesperson's estimated probability of winning the opportunity.
● total_current_rev: The projected revenue for this opportunity (in dollars).
● aai_label: Indicates whether the opportunity was labeled as "data" by the
salesperson.
